ports that she's not handing over the bowl. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urpthehotrod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RpTheHotrod</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/11/01 10:46:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> one reason...</span><hr size=1> One reason is because they don't have a main inv slot open. Yes, they are triggered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazraelmoonwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azrael Moonwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/13/01 6:47:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://cryofthewolf.tripod.com/azrael7.jpg width = 121 hieght = 315></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: one reason...</span><hr size=1> Althele is the only one that must be up. When you hand her the coin, the first NPC pops. When you hand the first NPC the Amulet, the next NPC pops, etc. A mistake I made the first time was handing the items in up to Teloa and then logging. If you do that you have to start over because all 3 quest NPCs except Althele will depop if no Reavers/Corruptor attack within 20-30 minutes or so. Then you will have an Amulet with no way to spawn Teloa and turn it in. Althele doesn't want the amulet.<br>
<br>
Another thing we found out yesterday is that all 3 will depop within 20-30 minutes if not attacked. I redid this part and we mezzed the reavers and fear-kited the corruptor, then killed the 2 reavers one at a time so the druids could live and we could do the quest again. Then a druid friend went down and also turned his items in to the druids all standing around Althele. He handed the Amulet to Teloa and gated back to us, and he stated she said the quest words like &quot;Please follow me for the final battle&quot; or whatever it was. About 2 minutes later no Corruper or Reavers spawned, so I ran back down to Althele and saw all 3 quest NPCs were gone. Apparently, they depopped in the 45-60 second window before the corruptor spawns.<br>
<br>
To sum this up, keep the coin from BW until you are ready to turn in to Althele and the other 3 druid NPCs. If you want to do this several times in a row for different druids, let the 3 spawned druid NPCs depop before you start again.<br>
<br>
EDIT : Another thing to note is the epic quest NPC Tarbul Earthstrider, a named hill giant. Yesterday, his pathing took him right through where we set up for the Corruptor twice. Just thought I'd add that so everyone who hasn't done this part yet knows it could get messy on that hill. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uazraelmoonwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azrael Moonwolf</A> at: 5/13/01 6:53:42 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umallansouthpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MallanSouthpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/14/01 10:14:36 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: one reason...</span><hr size=1> /agree Azrael<br>
<br>
We tried to do the quest multiple times and the unlucky druid who turned in their coin when all NPC's were already standing together promptly lost his coin (that would be me).  About 5 min later all the NPC's except Althele depopped, and then a ranger in our guild was able to successfully trigger the Corrupter and Reavers.  So hold on to your coin until the others are NOT present.<br>
